The paper deals with 3D face reconstruction using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of bump mapping, which is a technique commonly used in computer graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (cs.MM) and proposes a layered approach to separate global shape from mid-level details (cs.AI). Finally, the paper provides quantitative and qualitative evaluations of the proposed method (cs.LG).
